article.description: — Filip Rebraca had 25 points and 14 rebounds as North Dakota edged past Western Illinois 83-81 on Friday night.
article.headline: Rebraca lifts North Dakota over W. Illinois 83-81
article.linkText: Rebraca lifts North Dakota over W. Illinois 83-81
article.story: GRAND FORKS, N.D. -- — Filip Rebraca had 25 points and 14 rebounds as North Dakota edged past Western Illinois 83-81 on Friday night. Rebraca shot 11 for 12 from the foul line. Bentiu Panoam had 14 points for North Dakota (5-13, 5-7 Summit League). Caleb Nero added 12 points. North Dakota totaled 54 points in the second half, a season best for the team. Will Carius scored a season-high 34 points for the Leathernecks (2-12, 0-7), who have now lost eight games in a row. Colton Sandage added 18 points. Ramean Hinton had 10 points and seven rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
